Comedy can be a dangerous business, especially if you try to have some fun at Jada Pinkett Smith's expense. Minneapolis comedian Emma Dalenberg didn't watch the Oscar ceremonies on March 27 in which Will Smith slapped Chris Rock after the comedian made a joke about the actor's wife. Dalenberg was too busy organizing the Underground Roast Battle, where stand-ups take turns ripping one another with the kind of material that would make Dean Martin raise his martini glass. You've read your complimentary articles for this time period.
